# ML Training Rules

## Model Architecture

- DSCNN-L: 276 channels, 1 initial conv + 5 DS blocks, embedding_dim=276
- DS blocks: DepthwiseConv -> BatchNorm -> ReLU -> PointwiseConv -> BatchNorm -> ReLU
- Last DS block (Block 5): DW still uses BN+ReLU, only post-PW uses LayerNorm(elementwise_affine=False)
- Initial conv: Conv2d(1, 276, kernel=(10,4), stride=(2,1))
- DS Block 1 stride=(2,2), DS Blocks 2-5 stride=(1,1)
- Final layers: AvgPool -> Flatten -> output (B, 276). NO Linear projection.
- L2-normalization applied EXTERNALLY (F.normalize in ReprModel wrapper)
- DSCNN-S (64ch, 22K params): optional for ablation only

## Training Protocol

- Episodic batching with Triplet Loss (NOT cross-entropy)
- Batch: 20 samples x 80 classes, margin=0.5
- Optimizer: Adam, lr=0.001
- Scheduler: StepLR(step_size=20, gamma=0.5) -- halve LR every 20 epochs
- Total: 40 epochs x 400 episodes
- Train on MSWC (450 words from top 500; 50 held out for validation; 263 eval words never seen)
- Augment with DEMAND noise: probability=0.95, SNR fixed 5 dB

## Code Patterns

```python
# Always use torch.no_grad() for inference/enrollment
with torch.no_grad():
    embeddings = encoder(mfcc_features)

# Prototypes = mean of support embeddings
prototype = support_embeddings.mean(dim=0)

# L2 normalize embeddings before distance computation
embeddings = F.normalize(embeddings, p=2, dim=-1)
```

## Validation Strategy

- Validation set: 50 words from MSWC top 500 (words ranked 451-500). Training uses remaining 450.
- Run few-shot evaluation on validation words every 5 epochs
- **Best metric**: validation AUC (binary keyword vs non-keyword) on 5-way 5-shot episodes
- Use validation metric to select best checkpoint (not training loss)
- No early stopping -- run all 40 epochs, pick best by val AUC

## Checkpointing

- Save model state_dict, optimizer state, epoch, val_auc, and training loss
- Checkpoint path: `checkpoints/{model_name}_{epoch}.pt`
- Keep best checkpoint by val_auc + latest checkpoint
- Always log training loss and val_auc to TensorBoard

## Reproducibility

- Set random seeds at start: `torch.manual_seed(seed)`, `np.random.seed(seed)`, `random.seed(seed)`
- Default seed in configs/default.yaml: 42
- For N evaluation runs, use seeds [42, 43, ..., 42+N-1]
- Set `torch.backends.cudnn.deterministic = True` for GPU reproducibility
